transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you for calling Viagra. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: How are you doing? I just checked my bank, right,

Speaker 1: and there was a withdrawal from you guys for 169,

Speaker 2: or I guess it would be A-G-E-D.

Speaker 1: Can you check that for me?

Speaker 2: Of course I can. Yeah, of course, of course.

Speaker 1: Did I just get your full name, sir, and date of birth?

Speaker 2: Henry Jenkins, 1-20-49.

Speaker 1: So Mr. Jenkins, I see your prescription was for the quantity of 40 of the 100 mg Viagra A-G-V.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: It looks like the doctor has you on refills, and yeah.

Speaker 1: So it looks like a refill went through on the 28th, and that's why you were charged that.

Speaker 2: You have a few options here, whatever you'd like to do.

Speaker 1: Normally, what I recommend for patients who really don't want these to come monthly,

Speaker 2: or in their case, tri-monthly, we put an extended pause on it.

Speaker 1: That allows you to kind of just call in and place orders as needed.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so I could adjust your prescription for any future refills to be like that.

Speaker 1: Okay, but hold on.

Speaker 2: So you're sent it out, right?

Speaker 1: Correct.

Speaker 2: So it has been assigned a tracking number.

Speaker 1: Okay, okay, because I haven't gotten any information about that.

Speaker 2: When I heard that you took the money out of the bank, I went and checked my mail,

Speaker 1: and I didn't see nothing there.

Speaker 2: So it hasn't arrived yet, put it that way.

Speaker 1: Exactly, correct.

Speaker 2: Okay, okay.

Speaker 1: So when it's getting ready to arrive, you're going to send out a tracking number for me?

Speaker 2: Exactly, yep, and then you'll know when to expect it.

Speaker 1: Okay, okay.

Speaker 2: Now, like you said before, yeah, I would like to do that instead of just checking it out.

Speaker 1: When I need it, I can call you guys and, you know, kind of order it like that.

Speaker 2: Okay, great.

Speaker 1: So I'll put that pause under your account here.

Speaker 2: Okay, sir, I went ahead and did that for you.

Speaker 1: You're all set.

Speaker 2: Okay, good, good.

Speaker 1: Another question.

Speaker 2: 100 milligrams is the highest, right?

Speaker 1: Yes, 100 milligrams are the highest prescription medication you can get of the Viagra.

Speaker 2: Okay, all right.

Speaker 1: Oh, the AHGV.

Speaker 2: Exactly, yeah.

Speaker 1: Okay, all right.

Speaker 2: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 1: I'll be looking forward for that then, okay?

Speaker 2: Happy to help.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
